P0.4 Graceful Shutdown Implementation Notes:

Changes to internal/main.go:
1. HTTP mode now uses httpServer.Shutdown() instead of Close()
   - Shutdown() allows in-flight requests to complete
   - Uses 30-second timeout for graceful shutdown
   - Falls back to force close if timeout exceeded

2. Stdio mode removes os.Exit(0) from shutdown goroutine
   - Previously: goroutine called os.Exit(0) bypassing defers
   - Now: goroutine only calls shutdown(), lets main return naturally
   - server.Run() returns when context is canceled

3. Error paths use return instead of os.Exit(1)
   - Allows any defers in main() to execute
   - Cleanup services can properly stop

Impact:
- In-flight HTTP requests complete gracefully
- Background services (cleanup, cost monitor) stop cleanly
- No resource leaks from abrupt termination

This completes all P0 Critical items.
